## New Project: blanch
- **Replaces:** mozilla/bleach (52.4M downloads/month, 2.8k stars, deprecated by Mozilla Jan 2023, depends on unmaintained html5lib)
- **Why:** Massive download base. Officially deprecated. nh3 (Rust-based) exists but has different API and lacks linkify — not a drop-in replacement. html-sanitizer also exists but different API. No maintained drop-in replacement.
- **Package:** blanch (verified available on PyPI)
- **Features:** clean(), linkify(), Cleaner class, Linker class, CSSSanitizer, constants (ALLOWED_TAGS, ALLOWED_ATTRIBUTES, ALLOWED_PROTOCOLS). Zero dependencies (stdlib html.parser), full type annotations, Python 3.10+.
- **Compat layer:** blanch.compat.bleach (drop-in module replacement for `import bleach`)
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #799 (scaffolding), #800 (HTML parser), #801 (sanitizer/clean), #802 (linkifier + CSS sanitizer), #803 (compat layer + tests)

